{"title_page": "Jeff Yoo", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{BLP sources|date=August 2009}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Jeff Yu\n| image =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1978|10|30}}\n| height =\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber  =\n| youthyears1 =  \n| youthclubs1 = [[Averett University]]\n| years1 = 2000 \n| years2 = 2000 \n| years3 = 2001\n| clubs1 = [[VfL Osnabr\u00fcck]] \n| clubs2 = [[Ulsan Hyundai Horang-i]] \n| clubs3 = [[Jeju United FC|Bucheon SK]]\n| caps1 = 1 | goals1 =  0 \n| caps2 = 3 | goals2 =  0 \n| caps3 = 2 | goals3 =  0 \n| nationalyears1 =  \n| nationalteam1  =  \n| nationalcaps1  =    \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate = May 5, 2009\n| ntupdate =\n}}\n\n'''Jeff Yu''', or '''Yu Ji-Young''', (born October 30, 1978) is a former [[association football]] player.\n\nYu is the first American football (soccer) player to have played in the [[South Korea|Korean]] [[K-League]]. He represented [[Ulsan Hyundai Horang-i]] in 2000 and [[Jeju United FC|Bucheon SK]] in 2001.<ref>{{K League player|20000084}}</ref>\n\nYoo had a brief spell with [[VfL Osnabr\u00fcck]] in the German [[2. Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Fussball Daten|title=Jeff Yu|url=http://www.fussballdaten.de/spieler/yujeff/|language=German|accessdate=March 18, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccer Times|author=Wagman, Robert|title=McBride produces instant results with Preston|url=http://www.soccertimes.com/usteams/2000/sep18.htm|date=September 18, 2000}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{K League player}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yoo, Jeff}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American soccer players]]\n[[Category:K League 1 players]]\n[[Category:Ulsan Hyundai FC players]]\n[[Category:Jeju United FC players]]\n[[Category:American expatriate soccer players]]\n[[Category:American people of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:Averett University alumni]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{BLP sources|date=August 2009}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Jeff Yoo\n| image =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1978|10|30}}\n| height =\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber  =\n| youthyears1 =  \n| youthclubs1 = [[Averett University]]\n| years1 = 2000 \n| years2 = 2000 \n| years3 = 2001\n| clubs1 = [[VfL Osnabr\u00fcck]] \n| clubs2 = [[Ulsan Hyundai Horang-i]] \n| clubs3 = [[Jeju United FC|Bucheon SK]]\n| caps1 = 1 | goals1 =  0 \n| caps2 = 3 | goals2 =  0 \n| caps3 = 2 | goals3 =  0 \n| nationalyears1 =  \n| nationalteam1  =  \n| nationalcaps1  =    \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate = May 5, 2009\n| ntupdate =\n}}\n\n'''Jeff Yoo''', or '''Yoo Ji-Young''', (born October 30, 1978) is a former [[association football]] player.\n\nYoo is the first American football (soccer) player to have played in the [[South Korea|Korean]] [[K-League]]. He represented [[Ulsan Hyundai Horang-i]] in 2000 and [[Jeju United FC|Bucheon SK]] in 2001.<ref>{{K League player|20000084}}</ref>\n\nYoo had a brief spell with [[VfL Osnabr\u00fcck]] in the German [[2. Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Fussball Daten|title=Jeff Yu|url=http://www.fussballdaten.de/spieler/yujeff/|language=German|accessdate=March 18, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccer Times|author=Wagman, Robert|title=McBride produces instant results with Preston|url=http://www.soccertimes.com/usteams/2000/sep18.htm|date=September 18, 2000}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{K League player}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yoo, Jeff}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American soccer players]]\n[[Category:K League 1 players]]\n[[Category:Ulsan Hyundai FC players]]\n[[Category:Jeju United FC players]]\n[[Category:American expatriate soccer players]]\n[[Category:American people of Korean descent]]\n[[